content.problem:
The diagram shows traffic flow (cars per hour) at an intersection of 
four one-way streets. Find the possible values for the unknown flows 
$x_1$, $x_2$, $x_3$, and $x_4$.

center
tikzpicture[scale=1.2]
 % Nodes
 (A) at (0,2) {$A$};
 (B) at (2,2) {$B$};
 (C) at (2,0) {$C$};
 (D) at (0,0) {$D$};

 % External flows
 (-1,2) – (A) node[midway, above] {$500$};
 (B) – (3,2) node[midway, above] {$300$};
 (3,0) – (C) node[midway, above] {$400$};
 (D) – (-1,0) node[midway, above] {$600$};

 % Internal flows
 (A) – (B) node[midway, above] {$x_1$};
 (B) – (C) node[midway, right] {$x_2$};
 (C) – (D) node[midway, below] {$x_3$};
 (D) – (A) node[midway, left] {$x_4$};
tikzpicture
center
